</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F32D5F2DFFF2FFB1EDF2A652FCDAF80C" blockId="12.[151,1437,1373,1974]" pageId="12" pageNumber="485">
<emphasis id="C1E6833FFFF2FFB1EDF2A652FEFFF828" bold="true" box="[199,273,1913,1938]" pageId="12" pageNumber="485">Notes.</emphasis>
This species closely resembles 
<taxonomicName id="349224AEFFF2FFB1EF47A651FD11F82B" authorityName="Baker" authorityYear="1914" box="[626,767,1913,1937]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Makilingia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="485" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculata">
<emphasis id="C1E6833FFFF2FFB1EF47A651FD11F82B" box="[626,767,1913,1937]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="485">M. maculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in size and color pattern but differs in having the head more strongly produced and in the structure of the male genitalia.
</paragraph>
